title: Barrett leads No. 1 Ohio State to 49-7 win against Rutgers (Yahoo Sports)
text: Posts: 54,510 Barrett leads No. 1 Ohio State to 49-7 win against Rutgers (Yahoo Sports) J.T. Barrett threw three touchdown passes and ran for two scores in his first start of the season, leading No. 1 Ohio State to a 49-7 victory against Rutgers on Saturday night and ensuring at least two weeks of quarterback stability for the Buckeyes. Ohio State (8-0, 4-0 Big Ten) extended its winning streak to 21 games, best in the nation, and heads into its off week with no doubt who the starting QB will be when Minnesota comes to Columbus on Nov. 7. It will be a nice change for coach Urban Meyer, who started Cardale Jones in the first seven games of the season before making the switch to Barrett this week.
